34) Replace all occurrences of a specific word with another word in a string using regular expressions
in PHP.
&lt;?php
$text = &quot;PHP is fun. Learning PHP can be very interesting. I love PHP!&quot;;
$search = &quot;/\bPHP\b/&quot;;
$replace = &quot;Java&quot;;
$result = preg_replace($search, $replace, $text);
echo &quot;Original Text: $text&lt;br&gt;&quot;;
echo &quot;Modified Text: $result&quot;;
?&gt;
OUTPUT:
Original Text: PHP is fun. Learning PHP can be very interesting. I love PHP!&lt;br&gt;Modified Text: Java is
fun. Learning Java can be very interesting. I love Java!
